latestPosts.caption:
✨ From Numbers to Brushes ✨
This is the most nerve wrecking thing I’ve ever done but I guess here we go 🤞

7 years as a Chartered Accountant taught me structure, discipline, professionalism and resilience. But deep inside, I craved creativity, color, and connection.

It wasn’t an easy decision to leave behind a stable career especially financially but I knew I had to follow my passion for makeup—a world where I could transform not just faces, but confidence too. But ofcourse CA hu toh calculated risks and planning ke bina this was not happening. 

This journey has been full of late nights,super demanding job, endless practice, client calls at dawn / midnights and moments of doubt, but every step has been worth it. Today, I stand proud as a bridal makeup artist, living my dream and helping others shine on their special days. Aage ki dikhi jayegi !! I’m embracing the unknown, chasing dreams , figuring out what to do everyday and living life on my own terms 🚀 It’s scary, exciting liberating all at once 😍

I think we all are trying to figure out life. In our own ways. In our own timelines. Nobody really knows what they are doing completely and that’s okay 🫂

💡 To anyone stuck between comfort and passion, remember: it’s never too late to start chasing your dreams.

🎥 Watch my journey unfold and let me know—what’s the dream you’re ready to chase? 💭 Share it with some one who needs to see this ✨

latestPosts.caption:
When the Red Woman x Little Red Riding Hood met in multiverse! 🤌🏽

Getting our hair coloured together was hands down one of the best (and most chaotic) ideas we’ve had! 💇‍♀️ Could we have saved money by going separately on a weekday? Yes. Did we throw logic out the window for the vibes? Also yes.

From overanalyzing every shade, seeking each other’s dramatic approvals like it was a life-or-death decision, clicking a ridiculous number of photos, shamelessly hyping each other up, and lowkey nudging each other to ask for a discount — 10/10 would do again. 😂

Massive shoutout to the team at Ecoluxe for making us look fabulous. 🙌

Back to feeling like myself — which apparently starts with how my hair is doing. Who knew my emotional stability was stored in my roots? 😌

#BackToRed #HairTherapyIsReal #Redhead #LovingYouIsRed

latestPosts.caption:
I know this might ruffle a few feathers… 😅 but I just have to say it — a lot of the makeup you see on Instagram is often exaggerated just for content. It’s not always meant for real-life wear, especially not on actual clients!

So if you’re a professional MUA or a bride to be , it’s super important to understand the difference between a “reel look” and a “real look” 💯 What looks amazing on camera doesn’t always translate well in person.

Of course, there are exceptions:
1️⃣ If you’re doing makeup for an editorial, beauty shoot, or music video
2️⃣ Or if a client specifically asks for a certain trend

But when it comes to bridal makeup — stay cautious! 👰🏼‍♀️ Your bride’s photos are going to last a lifetime. The goal is timeless beauty, not a trend that makes it obvious what year she got married 😂

Let’s chat — what Insta makeup trends do you love or avoid when working on clients? Share below 👇🏼👇🏼👇🏼
